      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "# NoteTweet 0.7.0\r\n\r\nThis release makes NoteTweet much better for people who post regularly: you can use multiple X accounts, the composer now follows X's real length rules, thread parsing is more reliable, and mobile Obsidian works again on older Android WebViews.\r\n\r\n## Multiple X accounts\r\n\r\nAdd named accounts such as Personal, Work, or Project, keep each account's credentials in Obsidian Secret Storage, and choose a default for quick-post commands.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"900\" alt=\"NoteTweet settings showing Personal and Project X accounts\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d828cb8f-4f73-4768-a73f-210546556f02\" />\r\n\r\nThe composer starts with your default account, but you can switch the posting identity for an individual post without changing your global preference.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"900\" alt=\"NoteTweet composer with the Project account selected\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/40fa3828-9ab0-4308-bdb5-80b289f8957a\" />\r\n\r\nScheduled posts remain intentionally separate: they use the posting identity configured on your self-hosted scheduler.\r\n\r\nExisting credentials migrate into the new account model. Credentials already stored in Obsidian Secret Storage move automatically; older Secure Mode credentials keep the existing password-assisted migration flow.\r\n\r\n## Counts that match X\r\n\r\nThe composer now uses X's weighted text rules instead of JavaScript string length. In practice:\r\n\r\n- URLs use X's fixed URL weight, so a long URL can still fit.\r\n- CJK characters are weighted correctly.\r\n- Emoji families, combining marks, and other grapheme sequences are kept intact when splitting.\r\n- Automatic splitting no longer cuts through URLs or user-visible characters.\r\n\r\n| A long URL at the limit | CJK text correctly blocked over the limit |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| <img width=\"600\" alt=\"Long URL accepted with a zero remaining count\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c69e71f0-7ad7-4775-9488-306e0592f0d9\" /> | <img width=\"600\" alt=\"CJK post blocked with a negative remaining count\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4d56c4b7-0c7c-4f1c-839d-762009be0ce4\" /> |\r\n\r\n## Mobile reliability\r\n\r\nThe composer and other promise-backed UI flows now work in mobile WebViews that do not provide `Promise.withResolvers`. URL analysis also bundles its browser-safe implementation instead of relying on Node's `punycode` module.\r\n\r\nThe final build was exercised on Android 14 with Obsidian mobile, including composer opening, account selection, X-weighted URL/CJK/emoji cases, thread parsing, and encrypted credential migration.\r\n\r\n## More reliable Markdown threads\r\n\r\n`THREAD START`, `THREAD END`, and `---` separators are now parsed as Markdown lines rather than brittle substrings. The parser accepts LF and CRLF files, tolerates surrounding whitespace on structural lines, ignores marker-like text inside code blocks, and reports malformed thread structures more clearly.\r\n\r\n## Upgrade notes\r\n\r\n- Requires Obsidian 1.13.0 or newer.\r\n- Existing account credentials are preserved through migration.\r\n- No scheduler configuration changes are required.\r\n\r\nThanks to everyone who reported the original issues and helped make this release possible.\r\n\r\n**Full changelog:** [0.6.6...0.7.0](https://github.com/chhoumann/notetweet_obsidian/compare/0.6.6...0.7.0)\r\n",
